refactor(picker): split toggle_verb into dedicated per-kind functions

Replace the generic picker.toggle_verb(picker_name, entry) dispatcher
with three dedicated exports: picker.pr_toggle_verb, issue_toggle_verb,
and ci_toggle_verb. Each takes an entry directly and returns its own
precise union type (PRToggleVerb, IssueToggleVerb, CIToggleVerb) so
callers and luals get better type information.

Shared placeholder/load_more/value-type guarding is factored into a
private entry_value helper so the per-kind bodies stay focused on the
actual state-to-verb mapping.

Callsites in pickers.lua and the preload stub in pickers_spec.lua are
updated accordingly. picker_init_spec.lua is split into three describe
blocks mirroring the function boundaries.
